266
00:10:41,903 --> 00:10:44,272
Ms. Kim was the performer.

267
00:10:44,273 --> 00:10:46,243
Her acting was superb.

268
00:10:46,373 --> 00:10:47,712
It was really cool.

269
00:10:47,713 --> 00:10:49,873
Ms. Kim was great.

270
00:10:50,413 --> 00:10:52,243
- "It's splendid." - "It's splendid."

271
00:10:52,283 --> 00:10:55,513
(Slowly with the teacher)

272
00:10:55,713 --> 00:10:56,713
(Toto!)

273
00:10:58,983 --> 00:11:02,323
(Acting is interesting.)

274
00:11:03,493 --> 00:11:05,792
(It's fun...)

275
00:11:05,793 --> 00:11:08,032
(as much as...)

276
00:11:08,033 --> 00:11:09,533
(Mount Everest.)

277
00:11:10,433 --> 00:11:11,902
(When the Tin Man...)

278
00:11:11,903 --> 00:11:14,372
(volunteered to become the bridge to cross the river...)

279
00:11:14,373 --> 00:11:16,333
I'll become a sturdy bridge.

280
00:11:17,503 --> 00:11:19,673
(It was impressive.)

281
00:11:20,673 --> 00:11:24,843
(I have a favorite scene now.)

282
00:11:25,283 --> 00:11:27,182
(It's cool.)

283
00:11:27,183 --> 00:11:29,653
- I want to be good at it.
- You do.

284
00:11:29,813 --> 00:11:31,652
(Desire that blossomed from affection)

285
00:11:31,653 --> 00:11:33,283
I should work harder.

286
00:11:34,493 --> 00:11:37,292
(Even in the playground)

287
00:11:37,293 --> 00:11:38,992
(Nonstop practicing even at home)

288
00:11:38,993 --> 00:11:41,493
(Even the dad is helping out.)

289
00:11:42,163 --> 00:11:44,062
(I woke up early in the morning...)

290
00:11:44,063 --> 00:11:45,332
(and practiced alone...)

291
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:48,473
(with the script in my dad's warehouse.)

292
00:11:48,933 --> 00:11:51,003
(I will do it until I memorize it.)

293
00:11:52,003 --> 00:11:54,672
(Reviewing the rehearsal)

294
00:11:54,673 --> 00:11:57,582
Didn't we agree to stand on the right?

295
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:58,613
We did.

296
00:12:00,013 --> 00:12:01,752
(Studying the performance themselves)

297
00:12:01,753 --> 00:12:03,813
It's a shame, but I'm taking my leave.

298
00:12:04,523 --> 00:12:06,623
(The Witch's line)

299
00:12:07,423 --> 00:12:11,393
(The young actors and actresses improved by helping each other out.)

300
00:12:12,193 --> 00:12:16,233
(I feel proud of having performed from start to finish.)

301
00:12:17,163 --> 00:12:20,633
(It was nerve-racking yet fun.)

302
00:12:21,633 --> 00:12:26,072
(I gained the confidence that we could do it.)

303
00:12:26,073 --> 00:12:27,142
You can do it!

304
00:12:27,143 --> 00:12:29,212
The whirlwind dropped...

305
00:12:29,213 --> 00:12:32,783
(I want to show how hard we've worked.)

306
00:12:33,313 --> 00:12:35,483
(Let's score over 90 points at least.)

307
00:12:35,953 --> 00:12:38,423
(It'd be nice to have a standing ovation.)

308
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:40,582
(I'm confident...)

309
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:43,453
(to infinity and beyond.)

310
00:12:44,763 --> 00:12:45,862
We can do it.

311
00:12:45,863 --> 00:12:47,162
("The Wizard of Oz")

312
00:12:47,163 --> 00:12:49,862
Hooray! Let's go to Oz!

313
00:12:49,863 --> 00:12:52,763
(We worked hard, so we can do it!)

314
00:12:55,733 --> 00:13:00,003
(The day of the school arts festival)

315
00:13:01,543 --> 00:13:05,213
(Today is Yongheung Elementary School's school arts festival!)

316
00:13:05,913 --> 00:13:07,553
(Title: Yongheung Elementary School School Arts Festival)

317
00:13:11,183 --> 00:13:14,323
(A stage filled with sunshine)

318
00:13:15,953 --> 00:13:19,863
(The time for all the hard work to unfold)

319
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:24,602
- Have some apples, Kangnam.
- You're up early.

320
00:13:24,603 --> 00:13:26,933
- Kangnam.
- You guys are up early.

321
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:31,903
(The last breakfast is simple.)

322
00:13:33,773 --> 00:13:36,343
I used to have Jolly Pong with milk.

323
00:13:36,943 --> 00:13:38,012
- Jolly Pop? Or the recipe?
- Yes.

324
00:13:38,013 --> 00:13:39,843
- Jolly Pong.
- That's good.

325
00:13:42,213 --> 00:13:44,353
(Digging in)

326
00:13:47,153 --> 00:13:48,353
Today is important.

327
00:13:50,193 --> 00:13:52,922
I wonder what the kids will be like once they see the audience.

328
00:13:52,923 --> 00:13:55,762
(Worried the audience might make the students nervous)

329
00:13:55,763 --> 00:13:56,863
I'm scared they might freeze up.

330
00:13:57,903 --> 00:14:01,133
(Meanwhile, after washing up his dishes,)

331
00:14:02,503 --> 00:14:05,573
(he heads to the room first to get ready.)

332
00:14:06,803 --> 00:14:08,112
Helping out the acting class...

333
00:14:08,113 --> 00:14:10,173
made Hyun Wook more sociable.

334
00:14:10,913 --> 00:14:12,842
- He's changed...
- Totally.

335
00:14:12,843 --> 00:14:14,013
compared to the early days, right?

336
00:14:14,853 --> 00:14:15,952
This show was for the kids...

337
00:14:15,953 --> 00:14:17,083
- and Hyun Wook.
- Yes.

338
00:14:17,283 --> 00:14:18,752
- For real.
- Right?

339
00:14:18,753 --> 00:14:19,952
He's changed a lot, hasn't he?

340
00:14:19,953 --> 00:14:21,523
(Potato Teacher has grown.)

341
00:14:22,853 --> 00:14:25,523
(CO KUN joins after washing up.)

342
00:14:28,763 --> 00:14:29,963
Really, Kangnam.

343
00:14:30,593 --> 00:14:32,233
- Hyun Wook is...
- What about him?

344
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:35,373
I told you.

345
00:14:36,003 --> 00:14:37,673
- What?
- His snoring.

346
00:14:38,643 --> 00:14:39,803
His snoring?

347
00:14:40,973 --> 00:14:42,743
(Tired)

348
00:14:43,073 --> 00:14:44,443
Do I snore a lot?

349
00:14:44,943 --> 00:14:46,842
Simply put, you're a snorer.

350
00:14:46,843 --> 00:14:48,283
- Really?
- Last night...

351
00:14:48,613 --> 00:14:49,613
(Snoring)

352
00:14:50,353 --> 00:14:51,552
- For real?
- Yes.

353
00:14:51,553 --> 00:14:52,952
(Shocked)

354
00:14:52,953 --> 00:14:54,292
- It must be the fatigue.
- CO KUN.

355
00:14:54,293 --> 00:14:56,253
There's a reason I sleep in the caravan.

356
00:14:56,953 --> 00:14:58,062
You're this loud.

357
00:14:58,063 --> 00:14:59,192
- Stop lying.
- No.

358
00:14:59,193 --> 00:15:01,233
- He's serious.
- I'm not that...

359
00:15:01,793 --> 00:15:04,802
I don't snore that loudly.

360
00:15:04,803 --> 00:15:05,803
No, you do.

361
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:09,003
(Confirmation of damage)

362
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:12,243
(Snoring)

363
00:15:13,873 --> 00:15:16,873
(Victim KUN tossed and turned for a good while.)

364
00:15:17,713 --> 00:15:18,912
You're like "Dragon Ball."

365
00:15:18,913 --> 00:15:20,482
(Screaming)

366
00:15:20,483 --> 00:15:22,513
His hair is practically "Dragon Ball" in the morning.

367
00:15:22,953 --> 00:15:24,182
Your hair is all up.

368
00:15:24,183 --> 00:15:26,753
(Energetic bed head thanks to it)

369
00:15:27,553 --> 00:15:29,252
When we shared the room the first night,

370
00:15:29,253 --> 00:15:30,753
- you didn't snore at all.
- I see.

371
00:15:30,853 --> 00:15:32,393
It made me worried.

372
00:15:32,593 --> 00:15:34,663
You didn't snore when I had just joined.

373
00:15:37,063 --> 00:15:38,263
I must be tired.

374
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:42,232
- You're all washed up, right?
- Yes.

375
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:43,433
- And you, Kangnam?
- Same here.

376
00:15:44,343 --> 00:15:46,473
- You're not, Tae Ri?
- I'll hurry. No, I'm not.

377
00:15:48,043 --> 00:15:49,513
I'll just listen to music.

378
00:15:50,413 --> 00:15:51,613
CODE KUNST's songs.

379
00:15:54,513 --> 00:15:56,852
(Playing music)

380
00:15:56,853 --> 00:15:58,553
- "For The Gone." - Of course.

381
00:15:59,323 --> 00:16:00,552
I love this song.

382
00:16:00,553 --> 00:16:01,593
("For The Gone" by CODE KUNST, Choi Jung Hoon of Jannabi, Simon Dominic)

383
00:16:02,623 --> 00:16:03,952
Did we ever properly listen...

384
00:16:03,953 --> 00:16:05,262
- to music here?
- No.

385
00:16:05,263 --> 00:16:06,793
(One of Artist KUN's masterpieces)

386
00:16:08,263 --> 00:16:09,293
It'll...

387
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:12,133
- It'll be a lasting memory, right?
- Totally.

388
00:16:12,363 --> 00:16:13,403
Right now.

389
00:16:13,903 --> 00:16:15,703
Yes. This very moment, right?

390
00:16:18,703 --> 00:16:21,312
(The moment that will have a lasting impression,)

391
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:22,913
(like the crimson fall foliage)

392
00:16:25,843 --> 00:16:27,752
All right, let's get going.

393
00:16:27,753 --> 00:16:29,613
(The last day of work of the unforgettable fall)

394
00:16:30,913 --> 00:16:32,553
Tae Ri, you didn't see yesterday's night sky, did you?

395
00:16:32,883 --> 00:16:34,593
- No.
- I saw a shooting star.

396
00:16:34,793 --> 00:16:36,252
- You did?
- This place is full of stars.

397
00:16:36,253 --> 00:16:37,253
I made a wish.

398
00:16:37,453 --> 00:16:38,462
- What did you wish for?
- What did you wish for?

399
00:16:38,463 --> 00:16:39,963
"Let me go home fast."

400
00:16:40,623 --> 00:16:42,033
(Laughing)

401
00:16:42,263 --> 00:16:43,632
It was for our performance.

402
00:16:43,633 --> 00:16:45,933
But the moment I saw the shooting star, I thought,

403
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:47,932
"Tomorrow's going to be bomb."

404
00:16:47,933 --> 00:16:50,273
(Tomorrow's going to be bomb.)

405
00:16:50,673 --> 00:16:52,673
Maybe today's performance will make history.

406
00:16:53,903 --> 00:16:57,113
They might become your juniors in ten years.

407
00:16:57,243 --> 00:16:58,643
- Yes, you never know.
- For sure.

408
00:17:01,613 --> 00:17:03,883
- It's warm.
- What great weather.

409
00:17:05,553 --> 00:17:07,353
Today's weather is the best yet.

410
00:17:07,993 --> 00:17:10,853
To think that it's sunny today when it was crazy windy yesterday.

411
00:17:11,193 --> 00:17:12,623
Right? Today.

412
00:17:13,563 --> 00:17:15,032
("The Wizard of Oz")

413
00:17:15,033 --> 00:17:16,033
Hey, Tin Man.

414
00:17:16,034 --> 00:17:17,432
(Hi.)

415
00:17:17,433 --> 00:17:19,102
- Ha Yun.
- Hi.

416
00:17:19,103 --> 00:17:20,532
- Won Jin.
- Hi.

417
00:17:20,533 --> 00:17:22,172
- Ju Eun. Hyo Min.
- Hi.

418
00:17:22,173 --> 00:17:23,472
- Eun Soo.
- Hi.

419
00:17:23,473 --> 00:17:24,643
Kyung Mo.

420
00:17:25,343 --> 00:17:27,402
Guys, what day is it today?

421
00:17:27,403 --> 00:17:29,242
- The school arts festival.
- The school arts festival.

422
00:17:29,243 --> 00:17:30,312
The school arts festival, right?

423
00:17:30,313 --> 00:17:31,442
- Yes.
- We did our best...

424
00:17:31,443 --> 00:17:32,612
the past two weeks, right?

425
00:17:32,613 --> 00:17:33,642
- Yes.
- Yes.

426
00:17:33,643 --> 00:17:37,212
We're going to give it our best during our performance today.

427
00:17:37,213 --> 00:17:40,322
But before the performance, we'll do one last rehearsal.

428
00:17:40,323 --> 00:17:42,092
- Okay.
- Let's give it our all.

429
00:17:42,093 --> 00:17:43,093
- Okay.
- Okay.

430
00:17:43,094 --> 00:17:44,392
- Shall we start?
- Okay.

431
00:17:44,393 --> 00:17:45,423
(We can do it!)

432
00:17:46,863 --> 00:17:47,993
Eun Soo and Kyung Mo.

433
00:17:48,593 --> 00:17:49,593
Did you get a good night's sleep?

434
00:17:49,594 --> 00:17:50,662
- Yes.
- Yes.

435
00:17:50,663 --> 00:17:51,763
How do you feel?

436
00:17:51,803 --> 00:17:52,862
Happy.

437
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:54,032
- Are you happy?
- Sad.

438
00:17:54,033 --> 00:17:56,303
- Happy and sad at the same time?
- Yes.

439
00:17:56,473 --> 00:17:58,143
- Let's do our best.
- Okay.

440
00:17:58,673 --> 00:18:00,173
- Okay.
- Good.

441
00:18:00,573 --> 00:18:02,473
- Good luck.
- It keeps following me.

442
00:18:03,043 --> 00:18:04,613
You're not leaving today, are you?

443
00:18:05,443 --> 00:18:06,482
I am.

444
00:18:06,483 --> 00:18:08,013
Can't you leave tomorrow?

445
00:18:09,313 --> 00:18:11,382
We'll see each other after the performance,

446
00:18:11,383 --> 00:18:13,453
so don't worry about it and focus on the show.

447
00:18:13,553 --> 00:18:15,023
- Okay?
- Okay.

448
00:18:15,953 --> 00:18:17,293
Let's go, guys!

449
00:18:17,393 --> 00:18:18,522
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

450
00:18:18,523 --> 00:18:20,023
All right!

451
00:18:20,123 --> 00:18:21,363
Let's go!

452
00:18:23,163 --> 00:18:24,862
Let's begin.

453
00:18:24,863 --> 00:18:26,532
(The final rehearsal begins.)

454
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:27,533
All right.

455
00:18:28,103 --> 00:18:32,143
(Tae Ri and CO KUN are behind the stage.)

456
00:18:33,473 --> 00:18:34,573
The curtain opens.

457
00:18:38,713 --> 00:18:41,012
Good luck.

458
00:18:41,013 --> 00:18:42,052
(Good luck, Dorothy.)

459
00:18:42,053 --> 00:18:43,053
(Good luck.)

460
00:18:43,054 --> 00:18:44,623
She's so cute.

461
00:18:44,723 --> 00:18:45,883
Adorable.

462
00:18:52,023 --> 00:18:55,563
(Dorothy is stranded in the unfamiliar Land of Oz.)

463
00:18:58,133 --> 00:19:01,973
(Toto comes out after her.)

464
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:06,573
(Smiling as if he's their dad)

465
00:19:07,913 --> 00:19:10,642
(Dorothy and Toto are so cute together.)

466
00:19:10,643 --> 00:19:13,112
My goodness! This isn't Mungyeong.

467
00:19:13,113 --> 00:19:15,452
It's so brilliant and colorful!

468
00:19:15,453 --> 00:19:17,353
- Great.
- It's dazzling.

469
00:19:17,453 --> 00:19:18,583
It's dazzling.

470
00:19:19,983 --> 00:19:22,952
I find Eun Soo's new traits...

471
00:19:22,953 --> 00:19:25,223
every day.

472
00:19:26,823 --> 00:19:27,862
- Oh!
- Oh!

473
00:19:27,863 --> 00:19:28,933
- Oh!
- Oh!

474
00:19:29,263 --> 00:19:31,503
- They're good.
- It's a thick forest.

475
00:19:32,433 --> 00:19:34,772
Also, she keeps making sounds on the stage...

476
00:19:34,773 --> 00:19:37,502
to give others stability,

477
00:19:37,503 --> 00:19:40,372
so the other children must feel reassured enough...

478
00:19:40,373 --> 00:19:41,573
to act.

479
00:19:41,843 --> 00:19:43,213
And I think...

480
00:19:43,313 --> 00:19:46,883
she's great at looking after Toto.

481
00:19:47,143 --> 00:19:49,583
I feel like Toto also improved a lot,

482
00:19:49,683 --> 00:19:51,853
thanks to Eun Soo.

483
00:19:52,023 --> 00:19:54,953
But Kyung Mo is cute...

484
00:19:56,493 --> 00:19:58,363
just by existing.

485
00:19:58,663 --> 00:20:00,622
- Sniff, sniff!
- Sniff, sniff.

486
00:20:00,623 --> 00:20:03,533
Sniff, sniff. I smell something!

487
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:07,603
Sniff, sniff. I smell water!

488
00:20:08,103 --> 00:20:09,832
Let's save her!

489
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:10,872
(Smiling)

490
00:20:10,873 --> 00:20:13,272
My favorite part in the adapted version is...

491
00:20:13,273 --> 00:20:15,143
Toto's "The best!"

492
00:20:17,113 --> 00:20:18,783
The best!

493
00:20:20,013 --> 00:20:21,652
(The director's favorite scene)

494
00:20:21,653 --> 00:20:23,083
He gets cuter every day.

495
00:20:23,813 --> 00:20:26,753
Right! Tin Man, will you cut down those trees?

496
00:20:27,653 --> 00:20:29,322
Hyo Min turned out to be a natural on stage,

497
00:20:29,323 --> 00:20:32,023
so I felt really good...

498
00:20:32,363 --> 00:20:34,493
because I've been so concerned about him.

499
00:20:35,093 --> 00:20:36,632
With those shoes,

500
00:20:36,633 --> 00:20:39,833
the Emerald Castle and Oz will all be in my grasp!

501
00:20:40,303 --> 00:20:42,932
Ju Eun has always been good.

502
00:20:42,933 --> 00:20:45,043
Won Jin has always been good.

503
00:20:45,543 --> 00:20:47,843
I think they're doing well enough...

504
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:51,043
to surprise me every day.

505
00:20:52,043 --> 00:20:54,753
I'd also like to commend Ha Yun.

506
00:20:55,353 --> 00:20:58,053
No, I am an actual wizard.

507
00:20:58,123 --> 00:21:01,152
I've been lying because people wouldn't believe me...

508
00:21:01,153 --> 00:21:02,493
if I seemed normal.

509
00:21:02,893 --> 00:21:04,923
He used to be so shy.

510
00:21:05,163 --> 00:21:08,292
But Ha Yun has grown so much.

511
00:21:08,293 --> 00:21:09,293
(The late bloomer of Yongheung Elementary School)

512
00:21:10,493 --> 00:21:12,032
I'll be your bridge.

513
00:21:12,033 --> 00:21:14,202
My body made of tin will make a strong bridge.

514
00:21:14,203 --> 00:21:16,833
Go defeat the Witch and bring Dorothy back.

515
00:21:17,473 --> 00:21:19,642
With a little bit of confidence,

516
00:21:19,643 --> 00:21:23,743
Do Hyun will be one of the greatest actors.

517
00:21:25,743 --> 00:21:27,483
I sincerely hope...

518
00:21:27,583 --> 00:21:30,852
that acting on that stage will be a happy memory for them.

519
00:21:30,853 --> 00:21:31,853
(Hoping this will be remembered as a happy moment)

520
00:21:32,853 --> 00:21:35,653
Today is the day of the school arts festival.

521
00:21:36,253 --> 00:21:38,793
The best!

522
00:21:39,563 --> 00:21:40,863
Yes!

523
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:46,833
(The audience enters at 1pm.)

524
00:21:48,073 --> 00:21:50,833
(Crowded)

525
00:21:52,343 --> 00:21:55,773
(All the local seniors have come.)

526
00:21:57,313 --> 00:21:58,543
I'm a little nervous.

527
00:21:58,983 --> 00:22:00,282
It's a town festival.

528
00:22:00,283 --> 00:22:01,382
(Yongheung Elementary School's school arts festival)

529
00:22:01,383 --> 00:22:03,212
I'd be so nervous.

530
00:22:03,213 --> 00:22:04,883
(Their parents are also here.)

531
00:22:06,023 --> 00:22:09,293
(Eun Soo's dad)

