795
00:35:07,103 --> 00:35:08,633
- He's the Scarecrow.
- Scarecrow.

796
00:35:09,103 --> 00:35:10,273
The Scarecrow.

797
00:35:11,433 --> 00:35:14,473
These crows aren't afraid of me anymore.

798
00:35:15,103 --> 00:35:16,673
(Sad)

799
00:35:17,073 --> 00:35:18,413
Adorable.

800
00:35:18,773 --> 00:35:20,882
- Hi.
- Hi, the weather's good.

801
00:35:20,883 --> 00:35:24,082
Thank you for talking to me when even the crows ignore me.

802
00:35:24,083 --> 00:35:26,052
Can't you come down from there?

803
00:35:26,053 --> 00:35:29,223
No, I can't because of the pole on my back.

804
00:35:30,993 --> 00:35:32,762
We'll help you down.

805
00:35:32,763 --> 00:35:35,163
- In 1, 2, 3. Come down.
- Come down.

806
00:35:35,633 --> 00:35:39,033
(Acting enthusiastically)

807
00:35:40,403 --> 00:35:42,372
Let me say hi again. Hi.

808
00:35:42,373 --> 00:35:44,772
I'm made of straws, and I don't even know who I am.

809
00:35:44,773 --> 00:35:45,773
Who are you?

810
00:35:45,774 --> 00:35:47,602
I'm Dorothy, and he's Toto.

811
00:35:47,603 --> 00:35:50,443
To go back to our home in Mungyeong,

812
00:35:50,843 --> 00:35:53,012
we're on our way to the Emerald Castle.

813
00:35:53,013 --> 00:35:56,313
The Wizard of Oz can grant anyone's wish.

814
00:35:56,583 --> 00:35:58,412
Where is the Emerald Castle?

815
00:35:58,413 --> 00:36:01,653
Oz? Wizard? Wish? What's a wish?

816
00:36:01,953 --> 00:36:03,453
You don't know what a wish is?

817
00:36:04,023 --> 00:36:06,023
I don't know anything.

818
00:36:06,563 --> 00:36:09,163
I'm made of straws, so I don't have a brain.

819
00:36:09,393 --> 00:36:12,363
Maybe the Wizard of Oz can give me a brain.

820
00:36:12,963 --> 00:36:15,032
He's the slowest and calmest I've ever seen.

821
00:36:15,033 --> 00:36:17,232
- He's doing great.
- Scarecrow is the funniest.

822
00:36:17,233 --> 00:36:19,602
When my straws fall out, I need you to stick them back in.

823
00:36:19,603 --> 00:36:22,673
If not, I might blow away in the wind.

824
00:36:24,413 --> 00:36:27,313
Then, should we all go together?

825
00:36:27,443 --> 00:36:28,812
In 1, 2, 3.

826
00:36:28,813 --> 00:36:29,953
- Hooray!
- Hooray!

827
00:36:32,823 --> 00:36:35,082
Two laps.

828
00:36:35,083 --> 00:36:37,222
- Two laps.
- Two laps.

829
00:36:37,223 --> 00:36:38,923
- Two laps.
- Two laps.

830
00:36:39,463 --> 00:36:41,893
Two laps.

831
00:36:44,793 --> 00:36:49,503
(They go around in circles and meet the Tin Man.)

832
00:36:53,403 --> 00:36:56,772
Sniff, sniff. I smell something!

833
00:36:56,773 --> 00:36:59,113
Hi, will you help me?

834
00:36:59,343 --> 00:37:01,012
How should we help you?

835
00:37:01,013 --> 00:37:03,683
There's an oil can at my waist, so please oil my joints.

836
00:37:04,413 --> 00:37:05,513
Okay.

837
00:37:07,023 --> 00:37:09,393
Say, "Hiss."

838
00:37:10,253 --> 00:37:11,923
- Hiss.
- Well done.

839
00:37:12,223 --> 00:37:13,322
- Good girl.
- Hiss.

840
00:37:13,323 --> 00:37:15,163
Great job.

841
00:37:15,363 --> 00:37:16,733
- Hiss.
- Great.

842
00:37:17,233 --> 00:37:18,263
Hiss.

843
00:37:22,273 --> 00:37:23,503
That feels good.

844
00:37:24,703 --> 00:37:27,543
- He just ad-libbed.
- Amazing.

845
00:37:29,313 --> 00:37:30,843
Do Hyun is doing great.

846
00:37:31,773 --> 00:37:34,512
You guys are really kind.

847
00:37:34,513 --> 00:37:37,552
I may look like I'm made of tin, but I used to be a man.

848
00:37:37,553 --> 00:37:39,782
The evil Wicked Witch of the West put a curse on me...

849
00:37:39,783 --> 00:37:42,123
and turned me into heartless tin.

850
00:37:42,183 --> 00:37:43,692
What? The Wicked Witch of the West?

851
00:37:43,693 --> 00:37:47,022
I'll find the Wizard of Oz and ask him to send me back home...

852
00:37:47,023 --> 00:37:49,193
before the Wicked Witch gets here.

853
00:37:49,893 --> 00:37:51,433
Who's the Wizard of Oz?

854
00:37:51,893 --> 00:37:54,302
I need a brain, so I'm going to ask the Wizard of Oz...

855
00:37:54,303 --> 00:37:55,633
for a brain.

856
00:37:56,133 --> 00:37:59,073
You should also go to him and make a wish.

857
00:37:59,203 --> 00:38:00,972
Then, I'll ask for a heart.

858
00:38:00,973 --> 00:38:03,743
I want a warm heart so I can finally be happy.

859
00:38:04,773 --> 00:38:06,242
I'll still ask him...

860
00:38:06,243 --> 00:38:07,482
to give me a brain.

861
00:38:07,483 --> 00:38:08,812
Without a heart...

862
00:38:08,813 --> 00:38:11,982
If I don't have a brain and have a heart...

863
00:38:11,983 --> 00:38:13,083
If I don't...

864
00:38:13,853 --> 00:38:16,052
- That's all right.
- It's fine.

865
00:38:16,053 --> 00:38:17,153
I won't...

866
00:38:17,453 --> 00:38:19,623
I won't know what to do, even if I have a heart.

867
00:38:20,023 --> 00:38:21,023
There you go.

868
00:38:21,023 --> 00:38:22,023
(Thank you.)

869
00:38:22,893 --> 00:38:25,093
Okay, Tin Man. You can come with us.

870
00:38:26,633 --> 00:38:29,103
(Everyone, "Hooray!")

871
00:38:30,133 --> 00:38:33,803
(Surprised)

872
00:38:34,173 --> 00:38:36,413
There's a thick forest ahead of us.

873
00:38:36,673 --> 00:38:39,713
It's too dangerous to pass!

874
00:38:41,543 --> 00:38:42,912
Then, what should we do?

875
00:38:42,913 --> 00:38:44,983
(What should we do?)

876
00:38:46,483 --> 00:38:48,682
Tin Man, will you cut down those trees?

877
00:38:48,683 --> 00:38:51,123
I may not have a heart, but I know how to chop down trees.

878
00:38:51,853 --> 00:38:53,893
(Grunting)

879
00:38:54,723 --> 00:38:57,163
(Grunting)

880
00:38:58,993 --> 00:39:00,232
Yes!

881
00:39:00,233 --> 00:39:03,503
(They pass the forest, thanks to the Scarecrow's wisdom.)

882
00:39:04,373 --> 00:39:06,073
The best!

883
00:39:07,373 --> 00:39:10,873
(Lethal cuteness)

884
00:39:10,973 --> 00:39:13,212
- Excitedly!
- The best!

885
00:39:13,213 --> 00:39:14,683
Adorable.

886
00:39:14,843 --> 00:39:17,213
I didn't know you could jump so high.

887
00:39:18,113 --> 00:39:21,123
You could jump that high? Awesome.

888
00:39:21,583 --> 00:39:22,623
All right.

889
00:39:26,093 --> 00:39:30,993
(Dorothy and her friends enter a jungle.)

890
00:39:36,433 --> 00:39:38,872
(Scary Lion appears.)

891
00:39:38,873 --> 00:39:39,873
That's so cute.

892
00:39:40,403 --> 00:39:41,543
Is that the Lion?

893
00:39:43,373 --> 00:39:45,073
(Growling)

894
00:39:45,313 --> 00:39:46,313
(Roar!)

895
00:39:46,913 --> 00:39:48,812
- Toto!
- Okay.

896
00:39:48,813 --> 00:39:49,813
Stop!

897
00:39:49,813 --> 00:39:50,813
(Hitting the mean Lion)

898
00:39:50,814 --> 00:39:52,553
(Sobbing)

899
00:39:53,223 --> 00:39:54,583
He's crying.

900
00:39:54,953 --> 00:39:56,553
Stop being mean to Toto!

901
00:39:56,693 --> 00:40:00,463
No matter how scary you are, I'll protect Toto!

902
00:40:00,623 --> 00:40:02,862
I'm sorry. I was just scared...

903
00:40:02,863 --> 00:40:04,292
because Toto growled at me.

904
00:40:04,293 --> 00:40:06,103
I'm actually a coward.

905
00:40:08,063 --> 00:40:10,533
- Cheer up.
- Hey, Lion.

906
00:40:10,803 --> 00:40:13,602
We're on our way to the Wizard of Oz to make our wishes.

907
00:40:13,603 --> 00:40:14,973
Why don't you join us?

908
00:40:15,343 --> 00:40:17,113
He can grant wishes?

909
00:40:17,173 --> 00:40:19,713
Then, will he be able to give me courage?

910
00:40:20,213 --> 00:40:21,642
If he's capable of giving me a brain,

911
00:40:21,643 --> 00:40:23,583
I'm sure that's an easy wish for him.

912
00:40:23,783 --> 00:40:25,452
Then, let me come with you.

913
00:40:25,453 --> 00:40:28,483
I can no longer bear living without courage.

914
00:40:29,653 --> 00:40:31,022
(It's your turn.)

915
00:40:31,023 --> 00:40:32,823
Let's go and find him!

916
00:40:33,263 --> 00:40:35,793
(Hooray)

917
00:40:36,593 --> 00:40:38,392
Keep them up!

918
00:40:38,393 --> 00:40:40,062
(Maintaining their pose)

919
00:40:40,063 --> 00:40:42,233
Gosh, they are so cute.

920
00:40:44,773 --> 00:40:47,303
(The curtain closes, and the narrator comes in.)

921
00:40:47,503 --> 00:40:49,313
Okay, you can start saying your lines right away.

922
00:40:50,913 --> 00:40:52,643
The journey was peaceful...

923
00:40:52,783 --> 00:40:55,983
except for the time when the Tin Man stepped on a beetle.

924
00:40:56,283 --> 00:40:58,552
The Tin Man cried for so long...

925
00:40:58,553 --> 00:41:02,023
that his friends had to keep oiling his joints to prevent rust.

926
00:41:03,953 --> 00:41:05,092
- "But..." - But...

927
00:41:05,093 --> 00:41:07,393
the peaceful adventure didn't last so long.

928
00:41:12,833 --> 00:41:15,703
(She turns into the Wicked Witch of the West.)

929
00:41:16,433 --> 00:41:19,443
What do you think happened to Dorothy and her friends?

930
00:41:20,903 --> 00:41:22,873
Well done. You covered your face.

931
00:41:23,843 --> 00:41:25,573
(Nervous)

932
00:41:25,843 --> 00:41:28,213
What a twist. She was the Wicked Witch of the West.

933
00:41:31,283 --> 00:41:35,523
(Sneaking up)

934
00:41:38,223 --> 00:41:39,322
Smell fire.

935
00:41:39,323 --> 00:41:40,363
(Nudging)

936
00:41:40,693 --> 00:41:41,822
Sniff, sniff.

937
00:41:41,823 --> 00:41:43,592
I smell fire.

938
00:41:43,593 --> 00:41:46,403
What? Fire? It will burn all my straws!

939
00:41:48,033 --> 00:41:49,062
(Shouting)

940
00:41:49,063 --> 00:41:50,672
(Screaming)

941
00:41:50,673 --> 00:41:53,203
Dorothy, we finally meet.

942
00:41:53,473 --> 00:41:56,973
I knew you'd be on your way to find the Wizard of Oz!

943
00:41:59,073 --> 00:42:03,813
(Impressed to see the Wicked Witch in person for the first time)

944
00:42:06,223 --> 00:42:08,583
Wait, you're the Wicked Witch of the West?

945
00:42:08,653 --> 00:42:11,023
Yes, I am the Wicked Witch of the West.

946
00:42:11,593 --> 00:42:14,323
Your sister's death was an accident.

947
00:42:14,493 --> 00:42:17,193
The hurricane dropped the house there.

948
00:42:17,993 --> 00:42:19,562
That's not important.

949
00:42:19,563 --> 00:42:21,603
What I want is your silver shoes.

950
00:42:21,703 --> 00:42:24,533
What? But they're just regular shoes.

951
00:42:25,903 --> 00:42:27,003
How foolish.

952
00:42:27,203 --> 00:42:28,672
With those shoes,

953
00:42:28,673 --> 00:42:32,043
the Emerald Castle and Oz will all be in my grasp!

954
00:42:32,273 --> 00:42:35,343
If that's what you want, I cannot give you my silver shoes!

955
00:42:36,283 --> 00:42:38,113
(Fireballs)

956
00:42:38,953 --> 00:42:40,453
Dorothy, no!

957
00:42:41,483 --> 00:42:44,093
- Oh, no.
- Halt.

958
00:42:44,323 --> 00:42:46,423
Oh, dear. Ju Eun is so good.

959
00:42:47,893 --> 00:42:49,862
- That was impressive.
- Great job, guys.

960
00:42:49,863 --> 00:42:51,033
Great job.

961
00:42:51,163 --> 00:42:53,632
- The lake!
- We need the lake.

962
00:42:53,633 --> 00:42:55,003
- The lake.
- Let's set the lake.

963
00:42:55,973 --> 00:42:57,272
(Installing the lake)

964
00:42:57,273 --> 00:43:00,703
All right. Dorothy, come here and start.

965
00:43:00,873 --> 00:43:01,942
It's about to open.

966
00:43:01,943 --> 00:43:04,313
Good. You've got this. Just a second.

967
00:43:04,613 --> 00:43:05,772
Right away.

968
00:43:05,773 --> 00:43:08,342
- Okay.
- We're ready to go.

969
00:43:08,343 --> 00:43:09,752
In five seconds.

970
00:43:09,753 --> 00:43:11,282
Five, four...

971
00:43:11,283 --> 00:43:14,083
Open it now, please.

972
00:43:19,623 --> 00:43:23,233
(The Witch and Dorothy are fighting across the lake.)

973
00:43:24,733 --> 00:43:27,802
Dorothy is all the way across this lake.

974
00:43:27,803 --> 00:43:30,672
How should we defeat the Witch and bring Dorothy back?

975
00:43:30,673 --> 00:43:32,133
Let's rescue her!

976
00:43:32,603 --> 00:43:34,172
But the Wicked Witch of the West is too powerful.

977
00:43:34,173 --> 00:43:36,213
Even all of us won't stand a chance against her.

978
00:43:37,273 --> 00:43:39,343
(Pondering)

979
00:43:40,113 --> 00:43:42,782
The Wicked Witch is made of fire, so we can eliminate her with water.

980
00:43:42,783 --> 00:43:45,013
But how do we cross the lake?

981
00:43:46,553 --> 00:43:47,553
(Making up his mind)

982
00:43:47,554 --> 00:43:48,882
I'll be your bridge.

983
00:43:48,883 --> 00:43:51,192
My body made of tin will make a strong bridge.

984
00:43:51,193 --> 00:43:53,923
Go defeat the Witch and bring Dorothy back.

985
00:43:54,323 --> 00:43:56,632
You can't do that. As soon as your body touches water,

986
00:43:56,633 --> 00:43:58,763
you will become rusty and get stuck.

987
00:43:59,233 --> 00:44:02,433
Even if my body stops moving forever, I want to save Dorothy.

988
00:44:04,303 --> 00:44:05,403
That's so touching.

989
00:44:10,573 --> 00:44:12,243
Guys.

990
00:44:12,613 --> 00:44:14,613
I'll try crossing the lake.

991
00:44:14,743 --> 00:44:17,553
I have my strong legs,

992
00:44:17,653 --> 00:44:20,123
so I'll rescue Dorothy.

993
00:44:21,923 --> 00:44:25,323
- Good luck!
- Good luck!

994
00:44:26,793 --> 00:44:28,692
(He jumps over the lake with his strong legs...)

995
00:44:28,693 --> 00:44:29,793
(and defeats the Witch.)

996
00:44:35,103 --> 00:44:37,133
I can't believe you figured out my weakness!

997
00:44:38,533 --> 00:44:40,043
Water was my one weakness!

998
00:44:40,403 --> 00:44:42,743
There was so much more evil things yet to be done!

999
00:44:43,043 --> 00:44:44,813
Sadly, I'm gone.

1000
00:44:46,283 --> 00:44:48,242
- Lion succeeded it!
- Lion succeeded it!

1001
00:44:48,243 --> 00:44:50,383
- Thanks, Lion!
- Thanks, Lion!

1002
00:44:50,613 --> 00:44:53,182
- Go forward.
- Further.

1003
00:44:53,183 --> 00:44:55,552
- Guys, further.
- Further.

1004
00:44:55,553 --> 00:44:57,052
That's good. Sing the song.

1005
00:44:57,053 --> 00:44:59,223
- Close the curtain.
- Close the curtain.

1006
00:45:02,093 --> 00:45:05,392
(With courage, the Lion lends a hand)

1007
00:45:05,393 --> 00:45:09,162
(The Scarecrow's wisdom is so grand)

1008
00:45:09,163 --> 00:45:12,872
(The Tin Man's heart is warm and true)

1009
00:45:12,873 --> 00:45:16,642
(Let's set out together, me and you)

1010
00:45:16,643 --> 00:45:19,742
(Open wide, it clears my mind so bright)

1011
00:45:19,743 --> 00:45:24,012
(Fill the whole world with a blue light)

1012
00:45:24,013 --> 00:45:27,152
(A good friend with a heart so wide)

1013
00:45:27,153 --> 00:45:31,253
(With Dorothy by our side)

1014
00:45:31,623 --> 00:45:34,792
(With friends)

1015
00:45:34,793 --> 00:45:38,293
(By our side)

1016
00:45:40,933 --> 00:45:42,063
All right!

1017
00:45:43,603 --> 00:45:46,143
(They head back to the Wizard of Oz.)

1018
00:45:48,673 --> 00:45:50,442
My Eun Soo is such a cutie.

1019
00:45:50,443 --> 00:45:51,613
(Eun Soo's grandma)

1020
00:45:56,683 --> 00:45:57,853
Emerald Castle?

1021
00:45:58,053 --> 00:45:59,482
(Dorothy and her friends arrive at the Emerald Castle.)

1022
00:45:59,483 --> 00:46:00,552
That's cool.

1023
00:46:00,553 --> 00:46:02,553
(Dorothy and her friends arrive at the Emerald Castle.)

1024
00:46:06,393 --> 00:46:09,693
(Ha Yun's mom)

1025
00:46:14,133 --> 00:46:16,502
Sniff, sniff.

1026
00:46:16,503 --> 00:46:18,333
It's a new smell! Hi!

1027
00:46:18,473 --> 00:46:19,603
Hello.

1028
00:46:20,203 --> 00:46:23,073
We're here to meet the Wizard of Oz.

1029
00:46:23,213 --> 00:46:26,312
You must wear these glasses before meeting him.

1030
00:46:26,313 --> 00:46:28,613
He will come out only if you call him with these glasses on.

1031
00:46:31,053 --> 00:46:34,483
(The Gatekeeper hands out glasses.)

1032
00:46:36,593 --> 00:46:37,822
(But these were no ordinary glasses.)

1033
00:46:37,823 --> 00:46:38,823
Thank you.

1034
00:46:38,824 --> 00:46:40,923
(But these were no ordinary glasses.)

1035
00:46:42,933 --> 00:46:45,333
The glasses are too dark to see anything!

1036
00:46:46,603 --> 00:46:49,873
(Everyone is in confusion.)

1037
00:46:50,503 --> 00:46:52,032
- What?
- Who are you?

1038
00:46:52,033 --> 00:46:53,902
Scarecrow, is that you? Are you Toto?

1039
00:46:53,903 --> 00:46:55,472
Yes, I'm Toto.

1040
00:46:55,473 --> 00:46:57,043
In 1, 2, 3.

1041
00:46:57,143 --> 00:46:59,212
- Wizard of Oz!
- Wizard of Oz!

1042
00:46:59,213 --> 00:47:01,483
- Please open the gate!
- Please open the gate!

1043
00:47:03,553 --> 00:47:05,713
(Surprised)

1044
00:47:07,898 --> 00:47:08,898
In 1, 2, 3.

1045
00:47:08,899 --> 00:47:10,697
- Wizard of Oz!
- Wizard of Oz!

1046
00:47:10,698 --> 00:47:13,168
- Please open the gate!
- Please open the gate!

1047
00:47:15,176 --> 00:47:17,316
(Surprised)

1048
00:47:24,320 --> 00:47:28,060
(The gate to the Emerald Castle opens,)

1049
00:47:29,760 --> 00:47:33,930
(and the Wizard's shadow appears.)

1050
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:37,700
I am the great Wizard of Oz.

1051
00:47:38,170 --> 00:47:41,570
I will grant your wishes if you defeat the Wicked Witch.

1052
00:47:41,670 --> 00:47:42,699
The Wicked Witch?

1053
00:47:42,700 --> 00:47:46,210
But we had already defeated her on our way here.

1054
00:47:46,310 --> 00:47:48,379
That's not possible.

1055
00:47:48,380 --> 00:47:49,910
How did you manage to defeat her?

1056
00:47:50,010 --> 00:47:53,419
How did we defeat her? Start.

1057
00:47:53,420 --> 00:47:55,480
(We'll show you photos.)

1058
00:47:56,350 --> 00:47:57,749
Witch!

1059
00:47:57,750 --> 00:47:58,849
(Photo 1: Toto turns into the Wicked Witch.)

1060
00:47:58,850 --> 00:48:02,759
(Photo 2: The Witch and Dorothy fight.)

1061
00:48:02,760 --> 00:48:07,029
(Photo 3: The Tin Man volunteers to be the bridge across the lake.)

1062
00:48:07,030 --> 00:48:11,029
(Photo 4: The Scarecrow says no, shaking his head.)

1063
00:48:11,030 --> 00:48:14,999
(Photo 5: The Lion jumps over the lake and defeats the Witch.)

1064
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:17,309
(Photo 6: Everyone cheers.)

1065
00:48:17,310 --> 00:48:19,840
- Yes!
- Yes!

1066
00:48:21,110 --> 00:48:23,009
(Panting)

1067
00:48:23,010 --> 00:48:25,480
Will you grant our wishes now?

1068
00:48:26,150 --> 00:48:28,450
Still, I cannot...

1069
00:48:29,480 --> 00:48:33,290
Sniff, sniff. I smelled this earlier.

1070
00:48:33,720 --> 00:48:36,530
You smelled it earlier? That's suspicious.

1071
00:48:41,330 --> 00:48:42,330
Fine.

1072
00:48:42,630 --> 00:48:44,000
Oh, no!

1073
00:48:44,430 --> 00:48:45,629
- What?
- What?

1074
00:48:45,630 --> 00:48:47,240
(Ha Yun's older sister)

1075
00:48:47,740 --> 00:48:49,910
Wait, it's the Gatekeeper!

1076
00:48:50,940 --> 00:48:53,280
He's fake! You lied to us?

1077
00:48:55,640 --> 00:48:58,110
No, I'm an actual wizard.

1078
00:48:58,310 --> 00:49:01,219
I've been lying because people wouldn't believe me...

1079
00:49:01,220 --> 00:49:02,550
if I seemed normal.

1080
00:49:02,750 --> 00:49:05,120
Because everyone judges me by how I look.

1081
00:49:06,520 --> 00:49:09,689
If you really are the Wizard, grant our wishes.

1082
00:49:09,690 --> 00:49:12,260
I wish to have a brain so I can be smart.

1083
00:49:12,660 --> 00:49:15,860
I wish to have courage and be the king of all animals.

1084
00:49:16,770 --> 00:49:19,600
I wish for a heart with a warm soul.

1085
00:49:20,500 --> 00:49:22,740
I wish to go back home.

1086
00:49:25,840 --> 00:49:28,810
Your wishes have already come true.

1087
00:49:28,910 --> 00:49:31,249
The Scarecrow figured out how to defeat the Witch,

1088
00:49:31,250 --> 00:49:33,120
and he's wiser than anybody in the world.

1089
00:49:33,220 --> 00:49:34,849
The Tin Man who's willing to sacrifice himself for others...

1090
00:49:34,850 --> 00:49:36,520
has a warm heart.

1091
00:49:37,490 --> 00:49:39,519
The Lion defeated the Witch,

1092
00:49:39,520 --> 00:49:41,759
so he's the bravest king of animals.

1093
00:49:41,760 --> 00:49:42,760
Roar!

1094
00:49:44,230 --> 00:49:45,659
What about my wish?

1095
00:49:45,660 --> 00:49:47,900
I want to go back home.

1096
00:49:48,000 --> 00:49:49,199
That's simple.

1097
00:49:49,200 --> 00:49:50,369
See those silver shoes?

1098
00:49:50,370 --> 00:49:51,499
(Tapping)

1099
00:49:51,500 --> 00:49:53,770
Simply stomp three times, and say your wish.

1100
00:49:55,600 --> 00:49:56,870
What? Really?

1101
00:49:56,970 --> 00:49:59,270
I can finally go back home.

1102
00:50:00,080 --> 00:50:02,339
Scarecrow, Tin Man, and Lion!

1103
00:50:02,340 --> 00:50:04,250
Thank you so much!

1104
00:50:04,650 --> 00:50:06,820
- Make a circle!
- Cheer!

1105
00:50:07,580 --> 00:50:10,090
(Cheering)

1106
00:50:14,190 --> 00:50:17,630
- We'll never forget you, Dorothy!
- We'll never forget you, Dorothy!

1107
00:50:19,060 --> 00:50:20,600
And my friend, Toto.

1108
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:24,600
You won't be able to speak once we go back.

1109
00:50:25,530 --> 00:50:26,870
Is there anything you want to say?

1110
00:50:28,540 --> 00:50:31,269
Let me just say this before we go back home.

1111
00:50:31,270 --> 00:50:33,280
Thank you, friends!

1112
00:50:34,540 --> 00:50:37,380
Let's go to our home, where our loving family is.

1113
00:50:38,850 --> 00:50:40,449
Stomp!

1114
00:50:40,450 --> 00:50:41,450
(Tapping three times)

1115
00:50:41,451 --> 00:50:44,149
- In 1, 2, 3, 4.
- In 1, 2, 3, 4.

1116
00:50:44,150 --> 00:50:47,489
- Yes!
- Yes!

1117
00:50:47,490 --> 00:50:48,520
(Everyone got their wishes.)

1118
00:50:51,690 --> 00:50:52,790
Keep going.

1119
00:50:53,800 --> 00:50:54,860
That's great.

1120
00:51:00,440 --> 00:51:02,500
Let's go home!

1121
00:51:04,140 --> 00:51:08,080
The friends fulfilled their wishes all by themselves.

1122
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:11,780
If you also have a wish, try to look within.

1123
00:51:11,980 --> 00:51:14,650
You might already have the power to make it come true.

1124
00:51:17,620 --> 00:51:18,620
Oh, right!

1125
00:51:20,620 --> 00:51:22,520
Ms. Principal, what is your wish?

1126
00:51:26,490 --> 00:51:29,230
I wish to be ten years younger!

1127
00:51:31,000 --> 00:51:33,700
I wish to be ten years younger!

1128
00:51:33,900 --> 00:51:36,710
(A pretty desperate wish)

1129
00:51:37,010 --> 00:51:38,769
You saw Dorothy and her friends, right?

1130
00:51:38,770 --> 00:51:41,040
You must fulfill your own wish.

1131
00:51:41,780 --> 00:51:43,950
(No!)

1132
00:51:45,180 --> 00:51:47,520
That's it from me.

1133
00:51:47,650 --> 00:51:49,319
Bye, everyone!

1134
00:51:49,320 --> 00:51:50,820
- Bye!
- Bye!

1135
00:51:53,490 --> 00:51:56,189
(Bye, "The Wizard of Oz!")

1136
00:51:56,190 --> 00:51:59,389
All right, everyone. That was "The Wizard of Oz..."

1137
00:51:59,390 --> 00:52:02,860
by the students of the after-school acting class!

1138
00:52:03,700 --> 00:52:07,169
All right. Should we meet them one more time?

1139
00:52:07,170 --> 00:52:08,669
- Yes!
- All right.

1140
00:52:08,670 --> 00:52:10,640
Open the curtain!

1141
00:52:12,710 --> 00:52:16,280
(Time for a curtain call)

1142
00:52:17,080 --> 00:52:18,679
Everyone, bow!

1143
00:52:18,680 --> 00:52:21,519
Yes! Awesome!

1144
00:52:21,520 --> 00:52:23,020
That was fantastic!

1145
00:52:23,520 --> 00:52:24,890
They're so lovely.

1146
00:52:26,990 --> 00:52:30,590
- Bye!
- Give it up one more time, guys!

1147
00:52:32,190 --> 00:52:35,930
Please step back and bow once again.

1148
00:52:39,700 --> 00:52:41,000
One more bow!

1149
00:52:41,940 --> 00:52:43,609
Thank you for watching!

1150
00:52:43,610 --> 00:52:44,909
Bye!

1151
00:52:44,910 --> 00:52:48,609
Great work, everyone!

1152
00:52:48,610 --> 00:52:50,880
- You guys are the best!
- In 1, 2, 3, 4.

1153
00:52:52,050 --> 00:52:53,319
- Bye!
- The best!

1154
00:52:53,320 --> 00:52:55,120
- Bye!
- Bye!

1155
00:52:55,280 --> 00:52:56,280
Bye!

1156
00:52:56,750 --> 00:52:58,450
- Bye!
- How adorable.

1157
00:52:59,490 --> 00:53:00,890
They did so well.

1158
00:53:01,590 --> 00:53:02,619
It was entertaining.

1159
00:53:02,620 --> 00:53:04,090
Thank you.

1160
00:53:04,190 --> 00:53:06,699
We appreciate the audience...

1161
00:53:06,700 --> 00:53:08,860
for rooting for them until the very end.

1162
00:53:09,060 --> 00:53:11,230
Next year and even ten years from now,

1163
00:53:11,470 --> 00:53:13,769
I hope Yongheung Elementary School...

1164
00:53:13,770 --> 00:53:17,009
has festivals as incredible as this one.

1165
00:53:17,010 --> 00:53:19,209
I've been the North Pole Teacher, Kangnam.

1166
00:53:19,210 --> 00:53:21,940
Thank you, everyone!

1167
00:53:22,040 --> 00:53:23,279
Thank you!

1168
00:53:23,280 --> 00:53:25,010
(That's the end of the school arts festival.)

1169
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:31,149
Kids!

1170
00:53:31,150 --> 00:53:34,389
You did so well!

1171
00:53:34,390 --> 00:53:35,689
Won Jin!

1172
00:53:35,690 --> 00:53:39,390
Toto, you're literally the best!

1173
00:53:39,560 --> 00:53:41,929
You almost jumped a whole meter, didn't you?

1174
00:53:41,930 --> 00:53:43,369
I was watching the whole time.

1175
00:53:43,370 --> 00:53:44,570
You were fantastic.

1176
00:53:46,200 --> 00:53:47,200
The best!

1177
00:53:47,200 --> 00:53:48,200
(Great job.)

1178
00:53:48,970 --> 00:53:50,839
- Good work.
- Yes.

1179
00:53:50,840 --> 00:53:51,969
- Are you happy with it?
- Yes.

1180
00:53:51,970 --> 00:53:53,340
- It was fun, wasn't it?
- Yes.

1181
00:53:53,440 --> 00:53:54,980
How did you jump so far?

1182
00:53:55,280 --> 00:53:57,410
(Laughing)

1183
00:53:58,650 --> 00:54:01,450
Ju Eun, you're the best. You were the best Wicked Witch ever.

1184
00:54:03,220 --> 00:54:04,220
Good work.

1185
00:54:04,221 --> 00:54:05,889
I got choked up in the middle.

1186
00:54:05,890 --> 00:54:08,760
Right? I'm getting emotional.

1187
00:54:09,020 --> 00:54:10,990
I got emotional right from the get-go.

1188
00:54:11,090 --> 00:54:13,629
- When she opened the door. And...
- Right.

1189
00:54:13,630 --> 00:54:14,959
Did you see how she timed it to the squeak?

1190
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:16,459
- Right?
- It was incredible.

1191
00:54:16,460 --> 00:54:18,170
It was the most precise one yet.

1192
00:54:19,730 --> 00:54:23,140
(When Dorothy first appeared,)

1193
00:54:24,170 --> 00:54:26,539
(she opened it right on time for the sound effect.)

1194
00:54:26,540 --> 00:54:28,010
She timed that perfectly.

1195
00:54:29,440 --> 00:54:30,610
I'm about to cry.

1196
00:54:31,510 --> 00:54:32,650
I'm going to cry.

1197
00:54:34,550 --> 00:54:36,990
(Proud of her)

1198
00:54:37,590 --> 00:54:40,389
- Above all, I feel proud.
- Totally.

1199
00:54:40,390 --> 00:54:41,659
You all did great.

1200
00:54:41,660 --> 00:54:43,459
- It's all thanks to you.
- I'm proud.

1201
00:54:43,460 --> 00:54:45,060
- I'm so proud.
- Should we do this too?

1202
00:54:45,230 --> 00:54:49,499
(The teachers all worked hard.)

1203
00:54:49,500 --> 00:54:50,500
It was so...

1204
00:54:50,501 --> 00:54:53,770
You guys went through so much.

1205
00:54:54,700 --> 00:54:56,540
That's so cool. I can't believe we pulled it off.

1206
00:54:59,940 --> 00:55:02,610
It was the most perfect run ever.

1207
00:55:03,180 --> 00:55:06,550
The audience was also perfect.

1208
00:55:06,880 --> 00:55:08,080
It was a happy performance.

1209
00:55:08,280 --> 00:55:10,020
I want to clap for the kids.

1210
00:55:11,620 --> 00:55:14,060
Of course, acting well is important.

1211
00:55:14,420 --> 00:55:17,490
But I think what matters is that they remember...

1212
00:55:17,760 --> 00:55:21,699
what they did on the stage was beautiful.

1213
00:55:21,700 --> 00:55:24,769
And the kids did a great job...

1214
00:55:24,770 --> 00:55:27,540
of helping the adults experience that.

1215
00:55:27,970 --> 00:55:32,209
It was like watching...

1216
00:55:32,210 --> 00:55:33,210
a beautiful fairy tale.

1217
00:55:33,211 --> 00:55:35,640
(Like watching a beautiful fairy tale)

1218
00:55:36,180 --> 00:55:38,309
- It's over.
- It is.

1219
00:55:38,310 --> 00:55:39,509
Gosh.

1220
00:55:39,510 --> 00:55:40,849
The play is over.

1221
00:55:40,850 --> 00:55:43,820
(The after-school acting class's first performance ends.)

1222
00:55:48,220 --> 00:55:49,220
How do you feel?

1223
00:55:51,060 --> 00:55:53,960
Now that it's over, I'm pretty sad.

1224
00:55:57,630 --> 00:55:58,630
What did you think?

1225
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:00,199
It was perfect.

1226
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:01,539
- Right.
- They were natural.

1227
00:56:01,540 --> 00:56:02,669
- So natural.
- Yes.

1228
00:56:02,670 --> 00:56:03,670
I just thought they were cute.

1229
00:56:03,671 --> 00:56:04,910
They were smiling the whole time.

1230
00:56:06,810 --> 00:56:08,739
- Hi!
- Hi!

1231
00:56:08,740 --> 00:56:11,279
- Hi, kids!
- Hi!

1232
00:56:11,280 --> 00:56:14,319
Hey, it's the actors!

1233
00:56:14,320 --> 00:56:18,290
(The after-school acting class's graduation ceremony begins.)

1234
00:56:18,820 --> 00:56:20,490
What about Kyung Mo?

1235
00:56:20,590 --> 00:56:22,719
Where's Kyung Mo? Kyung Mo!

1236
00:56:22,720 --> 00:56:23,759
- Yes?
- Kyung Mo!

1237
00:56:23,760 --> 00:56:24,760
Hey, Kyung Mo.

1238
00:56:24,761 --> 00:56:28,060
(The last child, Kyung Mo, enters.)

1239
00:56:28,430 --> 00:56:30,870
You should have this.

1240
00:56:30,970 --> 00:56:33,029
- What's this?
- Snacks!

1241
00:56:33,030 --> 00:56:34,839
- You're the best, Ha Yun.
- Yes.

1242
00:56:34,840 --> 00:56:36,240
- I envy you.
- I mean it.

1243
00:56:38,940 --> 00:56:42,940
I think it's time to give them.

1244
00:56:43,340 --> 00:56:44,749
(Their covert mission begins.)

1245
00:56:44,750 --> 00:56:46,210
It glows in the dark!

1246
00:56:46,310 --> 00:56:49,950
Teachers, please turn around!

1247
00:56:50,120 --> 00:56:51,349
- What?
- Turn around, everyone.

1248
00:56:51,350 --> 00:56:53,050
- He wants us to turn around.
- We have a present.

1249
00:56:53,150 --> 00:56:54,589
- What? For us?
- What is it?

1250
00:56:54,590 --> 00:56:55,920
Please turn around.

1251
00:56:56,290 --> 00:56:57,989
- Don't look!
- Okay.

1252
00:56:57,990 --> 00:56:59,859
- You can never look.
- Okay.

1253
00:56:59,860 --> 00:57:01,699
- Keep your eyes forward.
- Okay.

1254
00:57:01,700 --> 00:57:02,700
(MC Lion does a great job.)

1255
00:57:02,800 --> 00:57:05,329
- Who is the yellow one for?
- Please follow my lead.

1256
00:57:05,330 --> 00:57:06,699
I can check out the yellow one.

1257
00:57:06,700 --> 00:57:08,639
(The older ones are secretly carrying out the plan.)

1258
00:57:08,640 --> 00:57:10,170
We should each stop a teacher.

1259
00:57:10,470 --> 00:57:11,739
Each person should...

1260
00:57:11,740 --> 00:57:13,210
(Hugging)

1261
00:57:13,840 --> 00:57:14,909
(Glancing over)

1262
00:57:14,910 --> 00:57:16,879
Don't turn around.

1263
00:57:16,880 --> 00:57:18,149
(Toto, the scary detection dog, sets off.)

1264
00:57:18,150 --> 00:57:19,809
- Don't turn around.
- Okay.

1265
00:57:19,810 --> 00:57:21,179
Don't turn around.

1266
00:57:21,180 --> 00:57:22,850
Look over here.

1267
00:57:23,350 --> 00:57:24,920
I have my eyes closed.

1268
00:57:25,720 --> 00:57:26,889
He's adorable.

1269
00:57:26,890 --> 00:57:29,020
- Mr. Lion.
- Are you all set?

1270
00:57:29,260 --> 00:57:31,030
- Are you the MC?
- Yes.

1271
00:57:31,430 --> 00:57:32,760
- How cute.
- Look over here.

1272
00:57:33,060 --> 00:57:35,059
- Look at the photo over there.
- Okay.

1273
00:57:35,060 --> 00:57:37,199
- Five, four...
- Look over here.

1274
00:57:37,200 --> 00:57:39,369
All set, Kyung Mo. We're ready.

1275
00:57:39,370 --> 00:57:41,099
We're all ready.

1276
00:57:41,100 --> 00:57:43,969
Please close your eyes and turn around.

1277
00:57:43,970 --> 00:57:45,169
- Close our eyes?
- Eyes closed?

1278
00:57:45,170 --> 00:57:46,639
We've turned around with our eyes closed.

1279
00:57:46,640 --> 00:57:48,640
Please open your eyes!

1280
00:57:50,001 --> 00:57:51,070
- Close our eyes?
- Eyes closed?

1281
00:57:51,071 --> 00:57:52,370
We've turned around with our eyes closed.

1282
00:57:52,371 --> 00:57:54,471
Please open your eyes!

1283
00:57:54,971 --> 00:57:56,841
- Gosh, what's this?
- What do we have here?

1284
00:57:57,411 --> 00:57:59,541
It's a message card.

1285
00:58:03,681 --> 00:58:05,150
Can we read it right now?

1286
00:58:05,151 --> 00:58:06,250
- Can we?
- Go ahead.

1287
00:58:06,251 --> 00:58:07,720
- Yes, read it.
- Really?

1288
00:58:07,721 --> 00:58:08,721
- Can we read it right now?
- Yes.

1289
00:58:08,721 --> 00:58:09,721
- You can.
- We all wrote something.

1290
00:58:09,722 --> 00:58:11,291
(A gift secretly prepared by the students)

1291
00:58:11,761 --> 00:58:13,020
Who didn't write on Potato Teacher's?

1292
00:58:13,021 --> 00:58:14,230
(Two days before the school arts festival)

1293
00:58:14,231 --> 00:58:15,261
Me.

1294
00:58:15,591 --> 00:58:17,161
- What about North Pole Teacher's?
- Me.

1295
00:58:20,161 --> 00:58:23,401
(Don't forget about us! It's a promise!)

1296
00:58:25,241 --> 00:58:28,411
(Thank you for making the classes fun.)

1297
00:58:29,411 --> 00:58:30,580
(Written with love with their small hands)

1298
00:58:30,581 --> 00:58:33,540
(I love you with all my might.)

1299
00:58:33,541 --> 00:58:36,551
How many days are left before the school arts festival?

1300
00:58:37,621 --> 00:58:38,621
Two days.

1301
00:58:38,751 --> 00:58:40,891
How do you feel with two days left?

1302
00:58:41,621 --> 00:58:44,290
- I'm sad.
- Why are you sad?

1303
00:58:44,291 --> 00:58:47,861
The teachers told us we didn't have homework...

1304
00:58:47,991 --> 00:58:51,431
during the school arts festival, but we'll start having it again.

1305
00:58:51,761 --> 00:58:53,661
- After the school arts festival?
- Yes.

1306
00:58:57,171 --> 00:58:59,901
What else are you worried about?

1307
00:59:00,071 --> 00:59:01,171
What else?

1308
00:59:06,841 --> 00:59:09,611
The teachers are leaving.

1309
00:59:09,951 --> 00:59:12,151
- Does that worry you?
- Yes.

1310
00:59:14,291 --> 00:59:16,191
It'll be heartbreaking.

1311
00:59:18,491 --> 00:59:20,791
I'll be really sad.

1312
00:59:22,891 --> 00:59:24,960
Do you think it'll be a lasting memory?

1313
00:59:24,961 --> 00:59:25,961
Yes.

1314
00:59:27,771 --> 00:59:31,200
I hope the teachers don't leave.

1315
00:59:31,201 --> 00:59:33,911
(In a way, the students who aren't familiar with farewells)

1316
00:59:35,411 --> 00:59:37,641
We put our hearts together and wrote it.

1317
00:59:38,341 --> 00:59:40,280
I'm the one who wrote "Potato Teacher."

1318
00:59:40,281 --> 00:59:42,280
(Bidding farewell with one heart)

1319
00:59:42,281 --> 00:59:43,310
- I didn't think...
- The yellow...

1320
00:59:43,311 --> 00:59:44,320
- you'd give it to me.
- is me.

1321
00:59:44,321 --> 00:59:46,450
- What?
- The yellow is me.

1322
00:59:46,451 --> 00:59:48,450
- The yellow.
- Yes, the yellow.

1323
00:59:48,451 --> 00:59:50,221
- Ms. Kim.
- So the yellow is you.

1324
00:59:50,661 --> 00:59:52,891
Who was this again? She wrote it.

1325
00:59:55,291 --> 00:59:57,030
- I wrote it.
- This one was by me.

1326
00:59:57,031 --> 01:00:01,101
(Reading each and every word on it)

1327
01:00:05,341 --> 01:00:07,811
Mr. CO KUN, you must keep it.

1328
01:00:08,441 --> 01:00:09,441
Of course.

1329
01:00:10,781 --> 01:00:13,610
It was empty, but now, it's all full.

1330
01:00:13,611 --> 01:00:14,911
Isn't it that?

1331
01:00:17,421 --> 01:00:18,651
She did it.

1332
01:00:18,781 --> 01:00:20,721
Are you guys leaving now?

1333
01:00:23,151 --> 01:00:27,260
(Thanks to you, I'm less shy now. Please remember us. From Ha Yun)

1334
01:00:27,261 --> 01:00:29,931
(Thanks to you, I'm less shy now. Please remember us. From Ha Yun)

1335
01:00:30,901 --> 01:00:32,661
Why are you teary, Ms. Kim?

1336
01:00:33,931 --> 01:00:35,270
Please make our wish come true.

1337
01:00:35,271 --> 01:00:36,900
I'm a very emotional person, you know?

1338
01:00:36,901 --> 01:00:38,540
- You're welling up, Potato Teacher.
- I'm teary.

1339
01:00:38,541 --> 01:00:40,241
- I'm Ms. Teary.
- Hurry up and cry.

1340
01:00:40,741 --> 01:00:42,040
Come on, cry.

1341
01:00:42,041 --> 01:00:44,281
- What's...
- Why are you crying?

1342
01:00:47,981 --> 01:00:50,081
- Oh, dear.
- What was it again?

1343
01:00:50,511 --> 01:00:51,821
What was it again?

1344
01:00:52,151 --> 01:00:54,221
Go stand over there.

1345
01:00:54,251 --> 01:00:57,761
Since you collected 20 stamps, we have gifts for you too.

1346
01:01:02,231 --> 01:01:03,691
- It's okay.
- Come on.

1347
01:01:04,001 --> 01:01:05,130
Don't cry.

1348
01:01:05,131 --> 01:01:07,930
(It's already time to say goodbye.)

1349
01:01:07,931 --> 01:01:09,401
Guys.

1350
01:01:09,701 --> 01:01:10,871
Okay.

1351
01:01:11,641 --> 01:01:13,371
Close your eyes and turn around.

1352
01:01:13,671 --> 01:01:14,971
- Turn around.
- Turn around.

1353
01:01:15,611 --> 01:01:17,741
- Don't cry.
- Don't cry. Wait there, okay?

1354
01:01:20,851 --> 01:01:26,781
(The classroom is filled with tears.)

1355
01:01:31,091 --> 01:01:32,361
Oh, dear.

1356
01:01:32,621 --> 01:01:35,590
(Tough Guy cries in secret.)

1357
01:01:35,591 --> 01:01:37,631
Why are you crying so much? It's okay.

1358
01:01:41,171 --> 01:01:42,301
- No.
- Guys.

1359
01:01:42,701 --> 01:01:43,870
- Okay.
- Turn around.

1360
01:01:43,871 --> 01:01:45,701
- Turn around.
- Turn around.

1361
01:01:45,871 --> 01:01:48,870
Because you all did...

1362
01:01:48,871 --> 01:01:51,041
a great job,

1363
01:01:51,441 --> 01:01:53,241
we teachers prepared the awards.

1364
01:01:54,011 --> 01:01:56,181
It's time for the award ceremony.

1365
01:01:56,411 --> 01:02:01,020
When your name is called, come to the front, okay?

1366
01:02:01,021 --> 01:02:04,860
- Okay.
- Lee Eun Soo.

1367
01:02:04,861 --> 01:02:07,091
- Get up here.
- Come over here.

1368
01:02:08,491 --> 01:02:12,600
"Full of Expression Award."

1369
01:02:12,601 --> 01:02:13,601
(Full of Expression Award: Lee Eun Soo)

1370
01:02:13,602 --> 01:02:14,971
Full of Expression Award.

1371
01:02:15,201 --> 01:02:18,070
"Lee Eun Soo is awarded..."

1372
01:02:18,071 --> 01:02:20,140
"for making the performance shine..."

1373
01:02:20,141 --> 01:02:23,310
"with her diverse expressions and actions..."

1374
01:02:23,311 --> 01:02:25,540
"in the after-school acting class."

1375
01:02:25,541 --> 01:02:28,650
From all the acting class teachers.

1376
01:02:28,651 --> 01:02:29,651
(A gift from the teachers)

1377
01:02:30,051 --> 01:02:31,950
- Great job.
- Be careful.

1378
01:02:31,951 --> 01:02:33,181
- Well done.
- Thank you.

1379
01:02:34,621 --> 01:02:37,291
(Answering well even while crying)

1380
01:02:37,521 --> 01:02:39,020
- Kyung Mo.
- Kyung Mo.

1381
01:02:39,021 --> 01:02:40,490
- Kyung Mo.
- Come up here.

1382
01:02:40,491 --> 01:02:43,130
"Very Best of the Best Award."

1383
01:02:43,131 --> 01:02:44,131
(Very Best of the Best Award: Kim Kyung Mo)

1384
01:02:44,132 --> 01:02:45,601
- Very Best of the Best Award.
- Very Best of the Best Award.

1385
01:02:45,861 --> 01:02:48,630
"Kim Kyung Mo is awarded..."

1386
01:02:48,631 --> 01:02:51,540
"for always cheering everyone up..."

1387
01:02:51,541 --> 01:02:54,470
"with a cute and bright smile..."

1388
01:02:54,471 --> 01:02:57,270
"in the after-school acting class."

1389
01:02:57,271 --> 01:02:59,481
Nice. How cute.

1390
01:02:59,711 --> 01:03:01,811
- The best.
- The best!

1391
01:03:03,781 --> 01:03:06,350
- That was adorable.
- Who is next?

1392
01:03:06,351 --> 01:03:07,380
Won Jin.

1393
01:03:07,381 --> 01:03:10,590
- Won Jin!
- With confidence.

1394
01:03:10,591 --> 01:03:11,591
With confidence. Here.

1395
01:03:11,592 --> 01:03:13,091
Okay. Your award.

1396
01:03:13,361 --> 01:03:16,360
"Happy Virus Award."

1397
01:03:16,361 --> 01:03:17,390
(Happy Virus Award: Jang Won Jin)

1398
01:03:17,391 --> 01:03:18,430
Won Jin.

1399
01:03:18,431 --> 01:03:20,130
Won Jin. Here's your gift.

1400
01:03:20,131 --> 01:03:21,200
Good.

1401
01:03:21,201 --> 01:03:23,001
- An RC car!
- It's what you wanted.

1402
01:03:23,901 --> 01:03:25,370
- Here.
- He likes it.

1403
01:03:25,371 --> 01:03:26,441
He's happy.

1404
01:03:26,841 --> 01:03:27,910
It made you stop crying, right?

1405
01:03:27,911 --> 01:03:28,970
(Stopped crying)

1406
01:03:28,971 --> 01:03:30,511
- All right.
- Let's see.

1407
01:03:31,111 --> 01:03:34,011
Your award. "Jack-of-All-Trades Award."

1408
01:03:34,351 --> 01:03:38,181
"For your full of emotion and amazing charm."

1409
01:03:38,321 --> 01:03:41,350
"For being the best Scarecrow."

1410
01:03:41,351 --> 01:03:44,420
"Lee Ju Eun is awarded for perfecting..."

1411
01:03:44,421 --> 01:03:46,320
"all three roles..."

1412
01:03:46,321 --> 01:03:48,790
"with different voices."

1413
01:03:48,791 --> 01:03:51,501
From all the acting class teachers.

1414
01:03:52,101 --> 01:03:53,301
Here you go.

1415
01:03:53,461 --> 01:03:55,230
Thank you.

1416
01:03:55,231 --> 01:03:57,601
Here's your gift, Ju Eun.

1417
01:03:57,671 --> 01:03:59,400
Our autographs are inside.

1418
01:03:59,401 --> 01:04:00,501
(After the tearful award ceremony)

1419
01:04:02,141 --> 01:04:04,141
Okay, Ju Eun.

1420
01:04:04,741 --> 01:04:05,741
Enough!

1421
01:04:07,011 --> 01:04:09,211
"Enough!" The Witch is here.

1422
01:04:10,851 --> 01:04:13,851
(Cheerful until the end)

1423
01:04:14,321 --> 01:04:15,321
(Crying)

1424
01:04:16,891 --> 01:04:18,891
- Guys.
- Why are you crying so much?

1425
01:04:20,091 --> 01:04:22,190
Guys, it's not like we're moving abroad...

1426
01:04:22,191 --> 01:04:23,761
or something.

1427
01:04:24,331 --> 01:04:26,230
It's a two-hour drive. Stop crying so much.

1428
01:04:26,231 --> 01:04:29,901
In the end, we're all Koreans living in the same country.

1429
01:04:31,101 --> 01:04:33,201
Aren't you Japanese, North Pole Teacher?

1430
01:04:35,441 --> 01:04:37,410
You're Japanese!

1431
01:04:37,411 --> 01:04:40,611
(Kangnam acquired Korean citizenship in 2022.)

1432
01:04:41,011 --> 01:04:42,881
- No, he's Korean.
- Listen.

1433
01:04:42,911 --> 01:04:46,121
No, I became a Korean citizen.

1434
01:04:46,251 --> 01:04:48,420
We're in Mungyeong...

1435
01:04:48,421 --> 01:04:51,621
while you'll be in Seoul.

1436
01:04:54,631 --> 01:04:56,661
(Laughing)

1437
01:04:57,531 --> 01:04:58,901
Look at her laugh.

1438
01:04:59,331 --> 01:05:00,970
You shouldn't be laughing.

1439
01:05:00,971 --> 01:05:03,170
- Hear me out.
- Why are you laughing, Ju Eun?

1440
01:05:03,171 --> 01:05:05,070
- I'm sorry.
- Us laughing doesn't matter,

1441
01:05:05,071 --> 01:05:06,600
- but not you.
- No, wait.

1442
01:05:06,601 --> 01:05:08,910
- The way she said it...
- Ju Eun.

1443
01:05:08,911 --> 01:05:09,941
Ju Eun.

1444
01:05:13,841 --> 01:05:16,080
Guys, how did you feel...

1445
01:05:16,081 --> 01:05:19,680
after performing in front of an actual audience today?

1446
01:05:19,681 --> 01:05:21,021
Can anyone tell me?

1447
01:05:21,191 --> 01:05:23,691
- I got a little nervous, - Is that so?

1448
01:05:24,621 --> 01:05:28,390
but I was happy it ended well.

1449
01:05:28,391 --> 01:05:30,460
Were you happy it ended well, even though you got nervous?

1450
01:05:30,461 --> 01:05:31,561
I was too.

1451
01:05:32,331 --> 01:05:34,100
- It was fun.
- Was it?

1452
01:05:34,101 --> 01:05:35,270
Was it fun?

1453
01:05:35,271 --> 01:05:36,870
He was confident and good.

1454
01:05:36,871 --> 01:05:37,970
- Totally.
- Right?

1455
01:05:37,971 --> 01:05:39,741
- Yes, he was the best.
- What about Ju Eun?

1456
01:05:39,801 --> 01:05:42,611
I was the same too. But...

1457
01:05:43,741 --> 01:05:45,580
We did well without any regrets.

1458
01:05:45,581 --> 01:05:47,710
- "Did well without any regrets." - Really?

1459
01:05:47,711 --> 01:05:49,411
- Amazing.
- You all did well.

1460
01:05:50,251 --> 01:05:53,450
I was nervous, but pulled it off well.

1461
01:05:53,451 --> 01:05:55,691
It's going to mean so much to me.

1462
01:05:56,021 --> 01:05:57,151
You're totally right.

1463
01:05:57,191 --> 01:05:59,560
It made you recall how we practiced together...

1464
01:05:59,561 --> 01:06:01,191
and all, right?

1465
01:06:01,661 --> 01:06:04,601
Can't you stay with us?

1466
01:06:14,941 --> 01:06:18,840
Ms. Kim, can I stay in Dorothy's house for a moment?

1467
01:06:18,841 --> 01:06:20,141
- What?
- Where?

1468
01:06:20,581 --> 01:06:23,350
- Over there.
- The restroom?

1469
01:06:23,351 --> 01:06:24,721
Go ahead.

1470
01:06:25,451 --> 01:06:26,851
You have to come back, though.

1471
01:06:27,481 --> 01:06:29,321
What is it? What?

1472
01:06:30,691 --> 01:06:33,020
- What are you doing?
- Mr. Choi, can I unwrap these?

1473
01:06:33,021 --> 01:06:34,021
Of course, you can.

1474
01:06:34,022 --> 01:06:35,031
(I'm curious about the gift.)

1475
01:06:36,161 --> 01:06:40,431
(Even when they're crying, they're curious about the gift.)

1476
01:06:41,331 --> 01:06:43,271
Eun Soo, how do you like brine shrimp?

1477
01:06:44,401 --> 01:06:46,301
I like it.

1478
01:06:46,801 --> 01:06:48,541
(Wailing)

1479
01:06:50,671 --> 01:06:52,940
That wasn't what we wanted.

1480
01:06:52,941 --> 01:06:54,010
Why?

1481
01:06:54,011 --> 01:06:55,611
(Approaching)

1482
01:06:57,111 --> 01:06:58,950
Do you like the color? Is it okay?

1483
01:06:58,951 --> 01:07:00,251
(Nodding)

1484
01:07:00,781 --> 01:07:03,050
Let's play baseball with it later. Okay?

1485
01:07:03,051 --> 01:07:06,020
(Potato Teacher understood Ha Yun better than anyone else.)

1486
01:07:06,021 --> 01:07:07,260
Kyung Mo, how was it?

1487
01:07:07,261 --> 01:07:08,660
- I loved it.
- Did you?

1488
01:07:08,661 --> 01:07:10,991
- You loved it.
- You jumped higher than others.

1489
01:07:11,501 --> 01:07:12,561
It was cute.

1490
01:07:12,701 --> 01:07:14,730
- You had springs in your feet.
- Exactly.

1491
01:07:14,731 --> 01:07:16,370
You had never jumped that high before.

1492
01:07:16,371 --> 01:07:18,541
(At a corner of the classroom...)

1493
01:07:21,171 --> 01:07:23,671
I didn't expect Hyo Min to do so.

1494
01:07:24,141 --> 01:07:25,741
I think Ju Eun's crying.

1495
01:07:28,111 --> 01:07:29,151
Really?

1496
01:07:29,581 --> 01:07:31,420
- I think so. She's hiding it.
- Really?

1497
01:07:31,421 --> 01:07:33,881
Gosh. I should go see her.

1498
01:07:36,051 --> 01:07:37,591
Really?

1499
01:07:37,891 --> 01:07:39,361
Are you coming with me, Won Jin?

1500
01:07:43,491 --> 01:07:45,100
Ju Eun.

1501
01:07:45,101 --> 01:07:46,461
(Ju Eun was crying alone.)

1502
01:07:46,731 --> 01:07:47,831
- Ju Eun.
- Yes?

1503
01:07:48,831 --> 01:07:51,841
My pretty Ju Eun. You did a wonderful job.

1504
01:07:52,571 --> 01:07:54,641
You didn't cry at all during the camping, did you?

1505
01:07:54,771 --> 01:07:56,710
You didn't cry when the others cried before.

1506
01:07:56,711 --> 01:07:58,441
But you came to the restroom to cry?

1507
01:07:59,741 --> 01:08:00,741
Ju Eun?

1508
01:08:01,611 --> 01:08:05,451
Thanks to you, I could cheer up and do it.

1509
01:08:05,921 --> 01:08:07,521
It was really hard for me too.

1510
01:08:08,551 --> 01:08:09,620
Thank you so much.

1511
01:08:09,621 --> 01:08:13,221
(Ju Eun)

1512
01:08:15,031 --> 01:08:18,761
Ju Eun had never gotten swayed away.

1513
01:08:19,801 --> 01:08:20,801
Hold on.

1514
01:08:20,802 --> 01:08:23,271
(Holding hands tightly)

1515
01:08:23,371 --> 01:08:24,871
Even during the camping,

1516
01:08:25,371 --> 01:08:29,570
she was the only one who said, "Please comfort my friends."

1517
01:08:29,571 --> 01:08:32,611
Because she was a person who said such a thing,

1518
01:08:35,481 --> 01:08:36,711
that moment lingers with me.

1519
01:08:38,821 --> 01:08:42,421
Everyone, we have spent two weeks together.

1520
01:08:42,621 --> 01:08:45,621
Your teachers would like to say a word too.

1521
01:08:45,921 --> 01:08:47,860
I want to go first.

1522
01:08:47,861 --> 01:08:48,861
- What?
- What?

1523
01:08:48,862 --> 01:08:50,330
I want to go first.

1524
01:08:50,331 --> 01:08:51,900
- Eun Soo will go first.
- Eun Soo, go ahead.

1525
01:08:51,901 --> 01:08:53,430
- Eun Soo will start.
- Ms. Kim.

1526
01:08:53,431 --> 01:08:54,431
Eun Soo.

1527
01:08:54,432 --> 01:08:58,901
I didn't know two weeks would feel this short.

1528
01:09:00,441 --> 01:09:04,211
If there is next time,

1529
01:09:04,371 --> 01:09:08,951
please stay with us for a little longer.

1530
01:09:10,151 --> 01:09:11,281
Okay?

1531
01:09:15,621 --> 01:09:17,151
(Standing up abruptly)

1532
01:09:18,521 --> 01:09:19,560
Suddenly?

1533
01:09:19,561 --> 01:09:20,890
- This way.
- She's crying.

1534
01:09:20,891 --> 01:09:23,830
(Hug me.)

1535
01:09:23,831 --> 01:09:25,661
- All of a sudden.
- There, there.

1536
01:09:25,831 --> 01:09:28,731
(Soothing)

1537
01:09:30,171 --> 01:09:31,501
Thank you, Eun Soo.

1538
01:09:34,511 --> 01:09:36,971
- Let me try it once.
- Listen, everyone.

1539
01:09:37,441 --> 01:09:39,341
You might have forgotten,

1540
01:09:40,841 --> 01:09:43,781
but you are my first students.

1541
01:09:44,211 --> 01:09:46,351
Imagine this, everyone.

1542
01:09:46,581 --> 01:09:48,651
In this world,

1543
01:09:49,251 --> 01:09:52,891
we go past Japan, Hawaii, and the Arctic.

1544
01:09:53,121 --> 01:09:55,931
There are so many people living in this world, right?

1545
01:09:56,861 --> 01:10:02,631
But we met like this in this fall for two weeks.

1546
01:10:03,001 --> 01:10:06,400
It's such a miraculous fate.

1547
01:10:06,401 --> 01:10:08,111
(They met by an incredible fate.)

1548
01:10:08,711 --> 01:10:11,840
Thanks to a very special fate,

1549
01:10:11,841 --> 01:10:13,740
we got to spend time together.

1550
01:10:13,741 --> 01:10:14,810
(To her first students that she'll never forget)

1551
01:10:14,811 --> 01:10:18,621
So, as you grow up,

1552
01:10:18,881 --> 01:10:20,781
I hope these two weeks together...

1553
01:10:21,321 --> 01:10:24,391
will give you strength.

1554
01:10:25,361 --> 01:10:28,891
As we get older and navigate our social lives,

1555
01:10:29,191 --> 01:10:32,161
we tend to think, "I lack in this or that area."

1556
01:10:32,401 --> 01:10:36,101
But this story tells us that we actually have it all inside.

1557
01:10:36,871 --> 01:10:41,271
That's the moral of "The Wizard of Oz."

1558
01:10:41,671 --> 01:10:43,841
Just like how adults know about the story's lesson,

1559
01:10:43,971 --> 01:10:46,541
I hope the kids will think one day,

1560
01:10:49,081 --> 01:10:50,981
"Yes. I'm perfect as is."

1561
01:10:52,651 --> 01:10:55,020
I hope they will live...

1562
01:10:55,021 --> 01:10:57,721
with the mind of loving themselves.

1563
01:11:02,891 --> 01:11:05,431
(Can I go across it here?)

1564
01:11:07,031 --> 01:11:11,601
The power of firsts is amazing.

1565
01:11:12,201 --> 01:11:14,071
It generates feelings that weren't there before.

1566
01:11:16,011 --> 01:11:17,040
Gosh.

1567
01:11:17,041 --> 01:11:19,310
I hope this class was special...

1568
01:11:19,311 --> 01:11:21,581
where they experienced things they never had before.

1569
01:11:23,681 --> 01:11:25,280
The witch flower has bloomed!

1570
01:11:25,281 --> 01:11:28,221
They acted as someone other than themselves.

1571
01:11:28,491 --> 01:11:29,491
What?

1572
01:11:29,492 --> 01:11:32,191
By doing so, they could think about themselves.

1573
01:11:34,731 --> 01:11:37,090
About what they're good at and what they can do.

1574
01:11:37,091 --> 01:11:38,160
(This moment was new to everyone.)

1575
01:11:38,161 --> 01:11:40,531
- I hope it was time for them...
- Lion succeeded it!

1576
01:11:40,831 --> 01:11:44,130
- to learn such a thing.
- We will never forget you.

1577
01:11:44,131 --> 01:11:47,201
(What seeds did this moment plant in the kids?)

1578
01:11:49,811 --> 01:11:51,610
Has anything changed...

1579
01:11:51,611 --> 01:11:53,341
while taking the acting class?

1580
01:11:55,981 --> 01:11:58,081
I was timid,

1581
01:11:58,421 --> 01:12:00,221
but I think I got better.

1582
01:12:01,121 --> 01:12:05,321
Today, I performed with confidence.

1583
01:12:05,891 --> 01:12:08,390
I speak more clearly now.

1584
01:12:08,391 --> 01:12:10,661
And I think I'm more confident.

1585
01:12:11,501 --> 01:12:14,401
I've gotten closer to my friends.

1586
01:12:15,331 --> 01:12:16,971
By not looking at the script,

1587
01:12:17,101 --> 01:12:19,471
my memory has improved.

1588
01:12:20,971 --> 01:12:22,511
The best!

1589
01:12:24,741 --> 01:12:26,681
- Kyung Mo.
- Mr. CO KUN.

1590
01:12:27,641 --> 01:12:30,410
You can cry a lot at home.

1591
01:12:30,411 --> 01:12:31,481
Okay.

1592
01:12:33,251 --> 01:12:34,751
Thank you, Kyung Mo.

1593
01:12:34,891 --> 01:12:36,551
- Okay?
- Teacher.

1594
01:12:39,991 --> 01:12:41,291
Let's see each other again, Ha Yun.

1595
01:12:42,161 --> 01:12:43,231
- Okay?
- Yes.

1596
01:12:45,461 --> 01:12:47,831
You have to get better at baseball. Okay?

1597
01:12:50,871 --> 01:12:53,201
- Thank you.
- Yes.

1598
01:12:53,341 --> 01:12:55,971
Gosh. How adorable.

1599
01:12:56,371 --> 01:12:57,640
(While thanking one another,)

1600
01:12:57,641 --> 01:12:58,711
You're so pretty.

1601
01:13:00,041 --> 01:13:02,011
- Thank you, Ju Eun.
- Is that so?

1602
01:13:03,011 --> 01:13:05,321
I love you so much. Okay?

1603
01:13:06,921 --> 01:13:07,951
Mr. Choi.

1604
01:13:12,461 --> 01:13:13,790
Good job. Okay?

1605
01:13:13,791 --> 01:13:15,690
(the kids graduate from the acting class today.)

1606
01:13:15,691 --> 01:13:17,060
Our Tin Man.

1607
01:13:17,061 --> 01:13:19,631
(the kids graduate from the acting class today.)

1608
01:13:22,531 --> 01:13:24,271
You were amazing today. Well done.

1609
01:13:28,711 --> 01:13:30,741
What is this?

1610
01:13:31,141 --> 01:13:33,340
- That's yours.
- Here.

1611
01:13:33,341 --> 01:13:34,540
Do you want me to take it too?

1612
01:13:34,541 --> 01:13:35,811
(Gift)

1613
01:13:37,711 --> 01:13:41,350
(And the gifts from the children to the teachers)

1614
01:13:41,351 --> 01:13:42,621
How nice it will be...

1615
01:13:43,421 --> 01:13:47,721
if I could express my feelings like the children?

1616
01:13:50,231 --> 01:13:54,631
I think, "How can I share my love with others?"

1617
01:13:56,001 --> 01:13:57,830
That's what's on my mind when I make music.

1618
01:13:57,831 --> 01:13:58,901
And...

1619
01:14:00,001 --> 01:14:01,740
the answer to the question was here.

1620
01:14:01,741 --> 01:14:02,811
So...

1621
01:14:04,271 --> 01:14:06,111
The ones who knew the answer...

1622
01:14:07,211 --> 01:14:09,451
weren't all those people with great knowledge...

1623
01:14:09,551 --> 01:14:12,551
or who have succeeded.

1624
01:14:13,221 --> 01:14:16,750
In fact, it was the children who knew the answer.

1625
01:14:16,751 --> 01:14:18,051
(The kids gave him the solution.)

1626
01:14:18,361 --> 01:14:22,060
There were moments I needed to say, "I love you,"

1627
01:14:22,061 --> 01:14:25,060
but I couldn't say it because I was shy.

1628
01:14:25,061 --> 01:14:26,931
And I regretted it so much.

1629
01:14:28,201 --> 01:14:31,201
They gave me uncontaminated, pure love.

1630
01:14:31,801 --> 01:14:33,671
It felt like a treatment.

1631
01:14:34,071 --> 01:14:36,911
It was a treatment, not just a healing moment.

1632
01:14:40,081 --> 01:14:42,880
It was calm yet fiercer than anyone else.

1633
01:14:42,881 --> 01:14:44,950
(It was a calm yet fierce moment.)

1634
01:14:44,951 --> 01:14:48,921
I went through a growing pain in that sense.

1635
01:14:50,851 --> 01:14:52,220
"The Wizard of Oz."

1636
01:14:52,221 --> 01:14:54,990
It felt like we were in such a fairytale.

1637
01:14:54,991 --> 01:14:56,530
(Our students did...)

1638
01:14:56,531 --> 01:15:01,000
I've never felt this proud before.

1639
01:15:01,001 --> 01:15:02,470
(an amazing job!)

1640
01:15:02,471 --> 01:15:04,941
These two weeks have been intense.

1641
01:15:06,371 --> 01:15:07,941
That was how it was like.

1642
01:15:11,511 --> 01:15:13,380
Even though I came here as a teacher,

1643
01:15:13,381 --> 01:15:15,481
it was another school for me.

1644
01:15:16,881 --> 01:15:17,911
I have...

1645
01:15:18,881 --> 01:15:20,420
I've learned so much from here.

1646
01:15:20,421 --> 01:15:21,690
(Let's remember this moment together forever!)

1647
01:15:21,691 --> 01:15:25,390
(After-school acting class)

1648
01:15:25,391 --> 01:15:26,720
Because we have to say goodbye,

1649
01:15:26,721 --> 01:15:30,831
this moment feels more precious and special.

1650
01:15:32,931 --> 01:15:35,100
(The Wizard of Oz. I look forward to our new days when we'll meet again.)

1651
01:15:35,101 --> 01:15:38,001
After a while, it will be concluded...

1652
01:15:38,201 --> 01:15:41,100
as memories in some form.

1653
01:15:41,101 --> 01:15:42,971
(Now, it's a memory, cherished in their own way.)

1654
01:15:43,411 --> 01:15:45,180
(Let's remember this moment together forever!)

1655
01:15:45,181 --> 01:15:48,480
I think that was the goal I had been trying to reach.

1656
01:15:48,481 --> 01:15:50,850
(I look forward to our new days when we'll meet again.)

1657
01:15:50,851 --> 01:15:52,521
(Ms. Kim)

1658
01:15:53,281 --> 01:15:54,281
Let's go.

1659
01:15:55,391 --> 01:15:56,391
Let's go.

1660
01:15:58,691 --> 01:16:00,390
It was astonishing every day.

1661
01:16:00,391 --> 01:16:02,761
(It was astonishing every day.)

1662
01:16:12,401 --> 01:16:15,510
I did my best like always, so it's all good.

1663
01:16:15,511 --> 01:16:19,811
(I did my best like always, so it's all good.)

1664
01:16:24,451 --> 01:16:31,221
(The after-school acting class ended in the fall of 2025.)

1665
01:16:37,591 --> 01:16:40,931
(Spring of 2026, after 4 months)

1666
01:16:42,301 --> 01:16:43,331
It looks good.

1667
01:16:43,531 --> 01:16:46,541
I'll get ready to clap.

1668
01:16:47,771 --> 01:16:49,340
You still remember it, Kyung Mo.

1669
01:16:49,341 --> 01:16:50,440
(He still remembers how to make an audio marker.)

1670
01:16:50,441 --> 01:16:52,081
One, two, three, clap.

1671
01:16:53,241 --> 01:16:54,540
I can't believe I'm doing this again.

1672
01:16:54,541 --> 01:16:55,550
(The students of the acting class)

1673
01:16:55,551 --> 01:16:58,320
I was in 4th grade, but I'm in 5th grade now.

1674
01:16:58,321 --> 01:16:59,380
(They are one grade more mature.)

1675
01:16:59,381 --> 01:17:01,520
My name is Lee Eun Soo.

1676
01:17:01,521 --> 01:17:02,650
(They have new hairstyles too.)

1677
01:17:02,651 --> 01:17:04,321
You permed your hair.

1678
01:17:04,751 --> 01:17:06,190
They only had one candidate...

1679
01:17:06,191 --> 01:17:07,820
for the school body president and vice president each.

1680
01:17:07,821 --> 01:17:09,531
- Really?
- Yes.

1681
01:17:09,931 --> 01:17:11,801
The best!

1682
01:17:13,131 --> 01:17:14,431
Roar!

1683
01:17:15,531 --> 01:17:17,230
I should have grown my nails...

1684
01:17:17,231 --> 01:17:18,840
in order to look like a lion.

1685
01:17:18,841 --> 01:17:21,541
Did you have new students this year?

1686
01:17:21,841 --> 01:17:23,171
No.

1687
01:17:24,511 --> 01:17:27,640
I'm in third grade, and I don't have lower classmates.

1688
01:17:27,641 --> 01:17:31,251
I didn't feel good because the school might close.

1689
01:17:31,751 --> 01:17:33,920
I hope the school stays.

1690
01:17:33,921 --> 01:17:36,021
This grass is natural too.

1691
01:17:36,821 --> 01:17:39,021
I don't understand why no one is coming to this school.

1692
01:17:40,921 --> 01:17:43,630
It has already been days...

1693
01:17:43,631 --> 01:17:46,261
since the show was aired, but still...

1694
01:17:47,631 --> 01:17:49,801
we haven't heard about any transfer students.

1695
01:17:51,101 --> 01:17:54,341
Has anything changed in the school?

1696
01:17:54,771 --> 01:17:57,441
Right. We have an acting class now.

1697
01:17:58,341 --> 01:17:59,541
Should we say it out loud?

1698
01:17:59,941 --> 01:18:01,881
- Start.
- Start.

1699
01:18:02,311 --> 01:18:04,610
- Everyone.
- Everyone.

1700
01:18:04,611 --> 01:18:07,321
I'll do my best in the acting class...

1701
01:18:07,581 --> 01:18:09,521
so that students will transfer to our school.

1702
01:18:10,391 --> 01:18:12,720
I'll prevent it from closing down.

1703
01:18:12,721 --> 01:18:15,561
What do you think a play is?

1704
01:18:15,661 --> 01:18:16,991
Will you tell us?

1705
01:18:17,191 --> 01:18:20,631
I think while doing a play, I laugh and chat.

1706
01:18:21,361 --> 01:18:22,431
It's fun.

1707
01:18:23,001 --> 01:18:26,871
A theater is like a playground.

1708
01:18:27,641 --> 01:18:31,211
After taking the acting class, I want to become an actor.

1709
01:18:31,981 --> 01:18:34,641
When I get an award in the future,

1710
01:18:34,981 --> 01:18:37,881
I'm going to say I started acting with Ms. Kim.

1711
01:18:38,381 --> 01:18:41,820
Ms. Kim, Potato Teacher, North Pole Teacher, and Mr. CO KUN.

1712
01:18:41,821 --> 01:18:43,291
I miss all of them.

1713
01:18:46,961 --> 01:18:49,430
I'm Dorothy, and I'm from Mungyeong.

1714
01:18:49,431 --> 01:18:50,431
(Dorothy: Lee Eun Soo)

1715
01:18:51,131 --> 01:18:53,000
The best!

1716
01:18:53,001 --> 01:18:54,131
(Toto: Kim Kyung Mo)

1717
01:18:54,631 --> 01:18:57,330
Right. Tin Man, will you cut down those trees?

1718
01:18:57,331 --> 01:18:58,331
(Scarecrow: Noh Hyo Min)

1719
01:18:58,601 --> 01:19:01,500
Even if my body stops moving forever, I want to save Dorothy.

1720
01:19:01,501 --> 01:19:02,511
(Tin Man: Kim Do Hyun)

1721
01:19:02,641 --> 01:19:05,440
I wish to have courage and be the king of all animals.

1722
01:19:05,441 --> 01:19:06,441
(Cowardly Lion: Jang Won Jin)

1723
01:19:06,841 --> 01:19:09,110
Yes, I am the Wicked Witch of the West.

1724
01:19:09,111 --> 01:19:10,151
(Narrator, Wicked Witch of the West, Munchkin: Lee Ju Eun)

1725
01:19:10,781 --> 01:19:13,180
Your wishes have already come true.

1726
01:19:13,181 --> 01:19:14,181
(Wizard, Gatekeeper: Cho Ha Yun)

1727
01:19:14,781 --> 01:19:16,491
You saw Dorothy and her friends, right?

1728
01:19:16,591 --> 01:19:18,821
You must fulfill your own wish.

1729
01:19:19,721 --> 01:19:21,490
Bye, everyone!

1730
01:19:21,491 --> 01:19:23,131
(Tae Ri, Hyun Wook, Kangnam, CODE KUNST, and Sung Jae)

1731
01:20:12,881 --> 01:20:15,680
(If you also have a wish, try to look within.)

1732
01:20:15,681 --> 01:20:18,551
(You might already have the power to make it come true.)
